Working with the mean

A group of 77 friends each have some playing cards. They work out that the mean number of playing cards they have is 66. Then 22 friends leave with an unknown number (xx) of playing cards. The remaining 55 friends work out that the mean number of playing cards they have left is 7.67.6.

How many playing cards (xx) were taken away from the group?

Answer:

The number of playing cards taken away is .

numeric
2 attempts remaining
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 3 / 3 points left]
Use the formula for the mean to figure out the total number of playing cards in the original group.
STEP: Find the total number of playing cards at the beginning
[−1 point ⇒ 2 / 3 points left]

We know that the mean number of playing cards the group originally had was 66. Since there are 77 people in the group we can find the total number of playing cards in the beginning using the formula for the mean:

mean=(number ofplaying cards (before))group sizenumber ofplaying cards (before)=mean×group size=(6)×(7)=42mean=(number ofplaying cards (before))group sizenumber ofplaying cards (before)=mean×group size=(6)×(7)=42
STEP: Find the total number of playing cards after the 2 people leave
[−1 point ⇒ 1 / 3 points left]

We are then told that 22 people leave. After that, the mean number of playing cards left is 7.67.6. We can then find out how many playing cards remain.

mean=(number ofplaying cards (after))group sizenumber ofplaying cards (after)=mean×group size=(7.6)×(5)=38mean=(number ofplaying cards (after))group sizenumber ofplaying cards (after)=mean×group size=(7.6)×(5)=38
STEP: Find the number of playing cards taken from the group
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 3 points left]

Now we can work out the number of playing cards which were taken from the original group.

number ofplaying cards removed=items before−items after=(42)−(38)=4number ofplaying cards removed=items before−items after=(42)−(38)=4

The correct answer is 44 playing cards.

Working with the range of a data set

Suppose a data set has a range of 44. If the minimum value in the data set is 4949, what is the maximum value in the data set?

Answer: The maximum value is .
numeric
2 attempts remaining
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]
Remember that the range is the difference between the largest and smallest values in a data set.
STEP: Use the range to find the answer
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

The range of a data set tells us how spread out the data are: it is the difference between the largest and smallest values. In this question, we do not know what the data values are, but we know that the range of the data is 44. We also know that the minimum value is 4949.

We can solve this question using the equation for the range:

range = maximum - minimumrange = maximum - minimum

However, for this solution let's think through the information that we have. The minimum value in the data set is 4949 and the range is 44. So the maximum value is 44 more than 4949.

maximum = minimum + range=49+4=53maximum = minimum + range=49+4=53

The maximum value is 5353.

Percentile and quartiles

Percentile is a value which tells us how far along through an ordered data set a certain value sits. Percentile is related to minimum and maximum values in a data set and to the quartiles.

From the dropdown menu below, choose the value which corresponds to the 25th25th percentile.

Answer: The 25th25th percentile corresponds to the .
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]
Starting at the minimum value and working up to the maximum value, percentile shows where a number sits in the data set. For example, the 50th50th percentile is halfway from the minimum value to the maximum value.
STEP: Use the definition of the quartiles
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

Quartiles break a data set up into four groups. We get those four groups by 'breaking' the data set when the percentile is a multiple of 25.

Percentile Position in the data Value in the data set
0th0th beginning minimum value
25th25th 1 quarter of the way first quartile
50th50th 2 quarters of the way median (second quartile)
75th75th 3 quarters of the way third quartile
100th100th upper limit of the data maximum value

For this question we have the 25th25th percentile. This corresponds to the first quartile.

The correct choice from the dropdown menu is: first quartile.

Applying percentile to a data set

The data set below has already been ordered for you. Which item is at the 75th75th percentile?

{a;f;m;n;n;q;s}{a;f;m;n;n;q;s}
Answer: The item at or closest to the 75th75th percentile is: .
one-of
type(string)
2 attempts remaining
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 2 / 2 points left]

Start by finding the rank of the item at the 50th50th percentile.

STEP: Determine the rank of the item at the 75th75th percentile
[−1 point ⇒ 1 / 2 points left]

We have a data set with 77 items in it, and the question asks us to determine the rank of the 75th75th percentile in the data set. For this we use the formula:

r=p100(n−1)+1r=p100(n−1)+1

where:

  • pp is the percentile value
  • nn is the number of items in the data set
  • rr is the rank (position) of the pthpth percentile in the data set

For this question, we have p=75p=75 and n=7n=7. Substitute these values into the formula above to find the rank.

r=p100(n−1)+1=(75)100×((7)−1)+1=75100×(6)+1=4.5+1=5.5r=p100(n−1)+1=(75)100×((7)−1)+1=75100×(6)+1=4.5+1=5.5

The rank of the 75th75th percentile in the data set is 5.55.5.

STEP: Use the rank of the 75th75th percentile to find the correct item in the data set
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 2 points left]

Now we need to find the item in the data set which corresponds to the 75th75th percentile. We use the rank to do this because the rank tells us the position of an item in an ordered list. In this case we want to know which item has a rank of 5.55.5.

But the rank of an item must be an integer because it represents a position. We need to find the closest position value to 5.55.5.

The rank value 5.55.5 is exactly between the fifth and sixth positions. So the 75th75th percentile corresponds equally well to both nn and other qq.

Either of these answers is acceptable for the item closest to the 75th75th percentile: nn or qq.

The range

Consider the set of raw data:

{6;10;6;10;8;6;7;5}{6;10;6;10;8;6;7;5}

What is the range of the data set?

Answer: Range:
numeric
2 attempts remaining
STEP: <no title>
[−2 points ⇒ 0 / 2 points left]

The most useful step towards solving any data problem is to sort the data first.

{5;6;6;6;7;8;10;10}{5;6;6;6;7;8;10;10}

The range of a set of data is the difference between the highest and lowest values in the set. In order to find the range, we should do the following:

  • Organise the data
  • Identify the lowest value
  • Identify the highest value and subtract them
Range=Highest value - lowest valueRange=10−5Range=5Range=Highest value - lowest valueRange=10−5Range=5

Therefore, the range of the data set is 5.

Calculating the range of a data set

A group of 1010 students count the number of marbles they each have. These are the data they collect:

25985972562598597256

Calculate the range of values in the data set.

Answer: The range of the data is .
numeric
2 attempts remaining
HINT: <no title>
[−0 points ⇒ 1 / 1 points left]

Start by finding the maximum and minimum values in the data set. Then use them to find the range.

STEP: Find the maximum and minimum values and calculate the range
[−1 point ⇒ 0 / 1 points left]

The range of a set of data values is the difference between the largest and smallest values in the set. So we need to find the difference between the maximum and minimum data values.

Firstly, we find the maximum value in the data set.

Maximum value =9Maximum value =9

Then we find the minimum value in the data set.

Minimum value =2Minimum value =2

Finally, we calculate the range of the data set.

Range=Maximum−Minimum=(9)−(2)=7Range=Maximum−Minimum=(9)−(2)=7

So the range of the data is 77.
